# Dev-only source and build-tooling directories at the *package root* —
# never needed at run time, only dist/ (already compiled) and the runtime
# deps in node_modules are. These would otherwise ship a TypeScript
# compiler's raw input, this package's own test suite, and its build
# scripts inside a one-click-install artifact.
#
# Anchored with a leading `/` on purpose: several plugins ship their own
# content directories literally named tests/, src/, or scripts/ under
# dist/content/plugins/**, and those are shipped product content, not this
# package's dev tooling (see the tsconfig.json precedent below — a bare,
# unanchored pattern here would silently drop that content the same way
# the built-in tsconfig.json exclusion once did).
/tests/
/src/
/scripts/

# @anthropic-ai/mcpb's built-in EXCLUDE_PATTERNS treats any file named
# `tsconfig.json` anywhere in the tree as a dev-config file and drops it —
# but dist/content/ ships one plugin's TypeScript eval-harness asset
# *as content*, not as this package's own build config. Un-exclude it so the
# bundled server actually finds it at startup instead of crashing with
# ENOENT (verified: `mcpb pack` silently produced a bundle missing this file
# until this line was added).
!dist/content/plugins/agentic-qe/skills/eval-harness/assets/typescript/tsconfig.json
